yourFriends is initialized and given memory address 97. totalFriends is initialized and given memory address 98. After being prompted with "Enter the number of people you know:", the user enters 200. 200 is assigned to yourFriends and stored in memory address 97. When totalFriends is assigned with yourFriends, the value 200 is now also stored in memory address 98. After printing totalFriends (200), totalFriends is multiplied by yourFriends and totalFriends is assigned with the product (40000). 40000 is stored in memory address 98, replacing the previous value of 200. The next print statement prints the new values of totalFriends. totalFriends is then multiplied by yourFriends one more time, resulting in a product of 8000000. totalFriends is assigned with the product (8000000) and 8000000 is stored in memory address 98. totalFriends is printed one last time. In memory, the variable yourFriends is assigned with 200 and stored at address 97. The variable totalFriends is assigned with 8000000 and stored at address 98.

